1. Go to Campsite's base install folder (e.g. /var/www/campsite) and run the following commands:

cd smarty_camp_plugins/
ln -s ../plugins/interview/smarty_camp_plugins/* .
cd ..

cd classes
ln -s ../plugins/interview/classes/* .
cd ..

cd template_engine/classes/
ln -s ../../plugins/interview/template_engine/classes/* .
cd ../..

cd template_engine/metaclasses/
ln -s ../../plugins/interview/template_engine/metaclasses/* .
cd ../..

cd admin-files
ln -s ../plugins/interview/admin-files/interview/
cd ..

cd css
ln -s ../plugins/interview/css/* .
cd ..

cd javascript
ln -s ../plugins/interview/javascript/* .
cd ..

2. Install the plugins/interview/install/sql/*.sql to campsite database.

3. If you have the demo installation, you can add the interview templates in this package by copying to templates folder. You will need to go to Campsite admin -> templates afterwards to register them.
cp -r plugins/interview/install/sample_templates/* templates

